# Cypress Standards

> Placeholder — expand with team conventions before implementing tests.

## Structure

- Page objects in `cypress/pages/` — specs never contain raw selectors
- API helpers in `cypress/utils/apiClient.js`
- Auth via `cypress/utils/auth.js` using `cy.session()` + API login
- Fixtures in `cypress/fixtures/` — no live credentials or JWTs

## Auth

- Prefer API login inside `cy.session()` for speed
- Use `validate` callback to detect expired sessions
- Never commit session cache or tokens

## Selectors

- Follow ADR-003 hierarchy: role → label → placeholder → text
- Selectors live in page objects only

## Reporting

- Allure metadata via `cypress/utils/allure.js`
- Results output to `cypress/reports/allure-results/`

